               <birth when="0408" syriaca-computed-start="0408-01-01" source="#bibl680-1">0408</birth>
               <floruit source="#bibl680-1" when="0488" syriaca-computed-start="0488">0488</floruit>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl680-1">BHO, 955- 56 (R. Raabe, 1895), 367-93. Jean Rufus, Plerophories, temoignages et revelations contre le concile de Chalcedoine ed. et trad. F. Nau dans PO, VIII.1 (1912), 126 n° 4, fin de Ia vie de Pierre. ' Les Vitae virorum de Brooks, CSCO (Syr. 8), 11- 12, ne donnent que quelques !ignes de Ia fin de sa notice. J.B. Chabot, dans Revue de /'Orient Latin 3 (1895), 367-93. D.M. Lang, "Peter the Iberian and his Biographers", Journal of Ecclesiastical History 2 (1951) , 158- 68; idem, Lives and Legends of the Georgian Saints (London 1976) 57- 80. ' ' BSO, II, 804 (E. Gabidzashvili).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Peter the Iberian was the son of the king of Georgia. He helped Nestorious preach a homily about the saints.  He went on a pilgrimage to Jerusalem and became a monk.  He became bishop of Maiuma in Gaza and was exiled to Egypt in 455. </note>
               <event type="veneration" source="#bibl680-1">
                  <desc>The saint is venerated on Syr. iacob., can. pr. 1..</desc>
               </event>
